<TD WIDTH=280 VALIGN="TOP">
IR's microelectronic relays consist of thyristor-based ChipSwitch<sup>&reg;</sup> products and
MOSFET based photovoltaic relays. The ChipSwitch<sup>&reg;</sup> is available in three packages
styles as an ideal solid state control device for AC loads, ranging from
milliamperes up to several hundred watts, in solenoids, electrical valves,
lamps, heaters, small motors, power contactors and annunciators. Our MOSFET
technology forms the heart of IR's series of photovoltaic relays used for
switching analog and digital signals in instruments, multiplexers, data
acquisition, automatic test equipment, telecommunications, and a wide variety
of general-purpose AC and DC signal switching functions.<p>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=180 VALIGN="TOP">
<IMG SRC="graphics/mer.jpg" ALT="Micro Electronic Relay" WIDTH=149 HEIGHT=128></td>
